						               													<description>The Sandwich Game is a fun way for family and friends to gather around the game table and compete to see who can eat their way to victory!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Work as a group to build community sandwiches then bid as individuals to see who eats each sandwich.  Be the champion by eating the most delicious sandwiches, or just have fun by making your opponent eat road kill and rotten tomatoes between two moldy croissants.  But beware, because your opponent might completely change what&amp;rsquo;s happening by throwing down a special napkin card at the last moment!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Sandwich game is a card game played in multiple phases.  Play starts in the Building Sandwiches phase where players take turns drawing cards and building communal sandwiches.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once a sandwich is completed play enters the Bidding phase where players take turns placing bid cards face down in front of any player (including themselves).  Once all players have finished placing bids, the bid score for each player is calculated to determine who eats the sandwich.  Eating the sandwich will reward that player with the point value of the sandwich (determined by the cards that make up the sandwich). Players can interrupt play and sour their opponent's plans by playing Napkin Cards.  These cards have specific effects on game play and scoring.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game end is determined by the number of players playing.  For 2 player games, the first player to 25 points wins.  In 3-4 player games the first player to 15 points is victorious.  For a 5 player game the Ultimate Sandwich Champion is the player with the most points after 5 sandwiches have been eaten.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
